I make this all the time but I add a couple ounces of goat cheese at the end and I simmer the shrimp in chicken broth till cooked thru. Try it that way if you think it needs a little extra flavor. It's even better the next day.

Rating: 3
Recipe is great. Peas make a frequent appearance in Northern Italian cuisine and really add just that bit of freshness you might crave while eating a heavy risotto. Instead of using the shimp stock, I used chicken broth- the water would make it taste too flat. Added about 2 tbsp of lemon juice from the zested lemon to add more freshness. Also, even though in Italian cooking you are not to have seafood and cheese together, I did blend the token parm at the end of the recipe since risotto is so much enhanced by it.

Rating: 2
I made this last night because I happened to have all of the ingredients on hand and I was looking for something yummy to feed a guest. I followed the recipe pretty much as written, except that I used fresh peas, used 2 shallots and 2 cloves of garlic instead of the onion, and added some cream and freshly grated parmesan at the end (in hopes of improving the flavour). Like other people have said, it lacks zip (in my opinion), and isn't really anything special. However, the two guys at the table both liked it (or said they did, anyway... ;)

