Rating: 3
I had to come up with a recipe for some frozen shrimp (already cooked), but I lacked a lot of the ingredients. Y'all might like to try modifying this very flexible recipe. I had the shrimp and the peas. Had to use chicked stock. Took the advice to add butter and parmesan at the end. Chopped about 3 cloves of garlic and a lot of ginger root instead of the onion. Used a bit more pepper in lieu of the chives. It was a huge hit -- sort of a Tuscan/Asian fusion. I heated the peas and shrimp only until warm. I think you could do many variations on this excellent basic recipe.

