Rating: 3
I made this for the second time tonight and can't for the life of me figure out why it doesn't have a better rating and more reviews. This is delicious. I did add the parmesan cheese and a little extra butter at the end like the previous reviewers and found that gave it the perfect extra touch. I will definitely be making this, perhaps not every week, but on a reasonably regular schedule.

Rating: 3
This is the first time I used a broth made from the shells when making shrimp risotto and it makes a huge difference. The dish had a much deeper shrimp flavor than when I use chicken stock. I put a bit of lemon juice in the broth which was unnecessary--the zest gives the dish plenty of lemon flavor. I also added two cloves of garlic to the recipe (with the onions), and added a little butter and a half cup of good grated Parmesan cheese right before serving, and both gave the dish the oomph that the other reviewer thought was lacking. Overall, very good.

